  "finding": "Topology mixing contributes to the broad P04c transfer, but the remaining widths are still far from a useful duplicate-readout-like closure. A1A3: best real `topology_median` res68 0.2636; Huber 0.2664 [0.2568, 0.2758], GBT 0.2717, shuffled 0.2734 A1_only: best real `cnn1d_waveform` res68 0.4824; Huber 0.5139 [0.4319, 0.6295], GBT 0.5189, shuffled 0.5203 A3_only: best real `hybrid_support_gate_cnn` res68 0.3954; Huber 0.3959 [0.3848, 0.4115], GBT 0.4026, shuffled 0.3983",
  "hypothesis": "If the A/B transfer floor is dominated by support topology rather than a missing waveform architecture, then future models that condition on B support cells should not beat the best P04t topology-specific lower bound unless they add independent A-side or calibrated energy information. A falsification test is to repeat this benchmark with an explicit A-side nuisance proxy held out by run and require a simultaneous res68 and full-RMS gain without shuffled-target improvement.",
